ews/483101/geoff-keighleys-opening-night-live-ad-prices", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Geoff Keighley\u2019s Opening Night Live raises ad prices, charging as much as $480K in 2025", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-21T15:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Fortiche, Riot Games/Netflix\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/Arcane_n_S2_00_07_49_14.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/impressions/476403/arcane-season-2-review-episode-act-1\">Arcane</a></em> takes place in the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/tv/476294/arcane-lol-easter-egg-season-2-league-show\">world of <em>League of Legends</em></a>, but whether or not the Netflix series is a direct adaptation of its lore is a little more up for debate. Since all the broad strokes have been similar, and all the crossover characters perfectly recognizable, it\u2019s easy to assume that the series is building up to a finale that gives its <em>League </em>characters the ending we expect. But there\u2019s nothing to say that <em>A", "id": 1561524, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/opinion/482290/arcane-netflix-league-legends-viktor-canon-dead-question-mark", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Arcane doesn\u2019t have to give League of Legends characters the ending you expect", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-21T14:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/polygon-siteicon-article.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">\u201cSpeedrunning\u201d in video games conjures images of frenetic sprints and glitchy hacks to go <em>as fast</em> as possible while skipping <em>as much</em> as possible.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">But what if you didn\u2019t <em>have</em> to go so fast?</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Lorn\u2019s Lure</em> is a first-person platforming exploration game. Even though it looks like a retro FPS, you don\u2019t fight: you just jump and climb and parkour your way through gobsmackingly massive structures.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">You can do this really fast if you want to: in fact, the game is made for <em>speedrunning</em>, with built-in timers for ", "id": 1561057, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/videos/481958/lorns-lure-speedrunning-game-lets-you-take-it-slow", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Lorn\u2019s Lure is a speedrunning game that lets you take it slow", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-21T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image composition: Cameron Faulkner/Polygon | Source images: Free League Publishing, Wizards of the Coast, Paizo Publishing\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/bestDNDgifts.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">Dungeons &amp; Dragons celebrated its 50th anniversary this year, and the tabletop role-playing game has never been more popular. If you\u2019re looking to buy a gift for a D&amp;D fan, there are plenty of great options at every price level, whether they\u2019re a seasoned Dungeon Master who\u2019s always looking to throw new challenges at their players or someone looking to keep track of all the characters they\u2019re playing \u2014 and the ones they just thought up.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">We have gift suggestions for people who are looki", "id": 1561058, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gift-guide/479722/best-dnd-gifts-dungeons-dragons", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best D&#038;D gift ideas for fans, players, and Dungeon Masters, too", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-21T13:47:22+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/vlcsnap-2024-11-21-12h51m36s081.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />